<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS -
        Component Reassembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Component Reassembly</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, use the correct Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new camshaft bushings and crankcase bores with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide a new bushing onto the Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet) .
                    Thread pulling screw, back-up nut, and Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer together. Tighten
                    expanding collet by turning back-up nut until bushing is securely held on tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650831" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/d0629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 316. Installation of cam bushing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply hole</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Backup nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing oil supply hole</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage and to ensure proper oil circulation through the crankcase, make
                        certain that all camshaft bushing oil holes are aligned with the corresponding oil supply holes
                        in the crankcase.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To aid in alignment of bushing and crankcase oil holes, use a marker to indicate oil
                    hole location on back-up nut of installation tool. Repeat this step for each camshaft bushing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all camshaft bushings through rear of crankcase. Pull bushings into place at
                    rear of crankcase by turning pulling nut on pulling screw. Remove installer tool and inspect oil
                    hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
